The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Air Deccan appoints Bardy as chief

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, Sept. 7: Air Deccan today announced the appointment of Warwick Brady (40) as the chief operating officer of the airline. Captain Gopinath, the promoter of the airline, follows a long list of Indian private airline operators who have in the recent past hired a foreign person to steer the operations of the company.

 Jet Airways, the leading private airline in the country, has over the years used the experience of experts from the global civil aviation industry to build for itself the largest market share among domestic airline operators including Indian Airlines.

 Be it New Delhi-headquartered Spicejet or Vijay Mallyas Kingfisher Airlines or Jeh Wadias Go Air, all have hired foreign a hand to set up operations recently. Go Air is yet to take off and the company is planning a launch very shortly. Warwick Brady has spent the last three years with Ryanair, a successful low-cost carrier in Europe. 




